Notes: FJC (First Jump) - Good exit, arch, canopy - go to DRCP
DRCP - Nice job! Cleared a malfunction!! (line over)
DRCP - Good jump, nice loud count, good job.
DRCP - Good exit, good arch, good DRC.

FFF - Good jump - solid and stable. Go to 5!!!!
5 sec delay - Nice arch, work on exit. OK for 10 sec.
10 sec delay - Weak arch on exit, corrected, nice solid freefall - good one!
10 sec delay (Relaxed Arch) - Excellent!! Nice relaxed arch. Work on leg position. Slight left turn. 15's next.
Relaxed Arch 180 turn RT - Good Job! 180 to 270 > turn RT. Stopped turn. 3500' good look, reach, & pull. Do 360 turn next & spot.
360 L, track, wave off - So-so exit, good 360 L (270). Nice track, good wave-off - BUT - pulled at ~2300'. ALTITUDE AWARENESS!! OK 30's.
Diving exit, back loop, delta, spotting - Good spotting. Good back loop + altitude awareness! Potatoe chipped a little on delta. Good wave off and pull. Do another 30 sec unless otherwise instructed.
360 L, 360 R (30 sec) - Good stable bomb out, nice 360 L, 360 R. Pinned right after. Work on body position and legs a bit. Good alt. aware. On to 45's.

Pin 360 L Pin 360 R - Good stable bomb out, kept right on heading until pin. Dropped left leg, spinning formation. Broke. 360 L no redock. Wave off, pull. Didn't 180 & track! Spot next. Make sure 180 & track.
RW 2 - Bomb out - pin by JM, left 360, re-dock 180 left turn on track (keep legs & arms out more) - next dive front loop / barrel roll & OFF STATUS.

45 sec delay - Stable bomb out base pin turned 375 broke and redock. Broke, attempted barrel roll. Front loop. Turn 180, track, slow wave-off pull 2600'. ** Joe has met all USPA min. std. perf...and can J/M himself **
